%20non-union%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat%20move%20might%20have%20unintended%20consequences%2C%20a%20legal%20expert%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20clock%20is%20ticking%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fcostco%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECostco%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20strike%20a%20deal%20with%2018%2C000%20unionized%20warehouse%20workers%20threatening%20to%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20been%20negotiating%20with%20the%20union%2C%20Costco%20Teamsters%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20expiration%20of%20their%20existing%20contract%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%20on%20January%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgainst%20that%20backdrop%2C%20the%20company%20announced%20this%20week%20in%20a%20widely%20circulated%20memo%20that%20its%202025%20Employee%20Agreement%2C%20which%20covers%20its%20nonunionized%20employees%2C%20would%20include%20successive%20pay%20raises%20that%20push%20compensation%20to%20over%20%2430%20an%20hour%20for%20workers%20at%20the%20top%20of%20its%20pay%20scale.%20A%20spokesperson%20from%20Costco%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrea%20Schneider%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Yeshiva%20University%20who%20is%20an%20expert%20in%20conflict%20resolution%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Costco%20likely%20made%20the%20announcement%20to%20lessen%20%26quot%3Bthe%20incentive%20for%20a%20strike%26quot%3B%20by%20assuaging%20concerns%20about%20stagnant%20wages.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECompensation%20is%20commonly%20the%20motivating%20factor%20behind%20a%20work%20stoppage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20the%20pay%20raise%20proposal%20could%20be%20the%20same%20one%20that%20Costco%20management%20offered%20the%20union.%20While%20it's%20a%20smart%20PR%20move%2C%20it%20might%20have%20unintended%20consequences%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20Costco's%20response%20to%20immediately%20grant%20the%20salary%20increases%20