hat%20Amazon%20admit%20wrongdoing%2C%20ends%20a%20lawsuit%20originally%20brought%20in%20California%20by%20a%20group%20of%20anonymous%20plaintiffs%20and%20As%20You%20Sow%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20that%20works%20with%20corporations%20to%20promote%20environmental%20and%20social%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20was%20later%20joined%20by%20the%20California%20attorney%20general's%20office%2C%20which%20sued%20Amazon%20under%20the%20state's%20Proposition%2065%20and%20its%20Unfair%20Competition%20Law.%20The%20AG's%20office%20will%20receive%20%24600%2C000%20of%20the%20settlement%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Amazon%20said%20the%20company%20has%20worked%20in%20good%20faith%20with%20the%20AG's%20office%20and%20is%20pleased%20to%20have%20the%20matter%20resolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20original%202014%20lawsuit%20alleged%20that%20Amazon%2C%20at%20one%20point%2C%20had%2027%20products%20for%20sale%20containing%20high%20amounts%20of%20mercury%2C%20sometimes%20at%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20times%20the%20allowable%20levels.%20Mercury%20is%20a%20neurotoxin%20that%20can%20cause%20prenatal%20defects%20and%20life-threatening%20kidney%2C%20brain%2C%20and%20central%20nervous%20system%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20knows%20which%20brands%20have%20already%20been%20flagged%20by%20regulators%20as%20violating%20FDA%20standards%20and%20California%20health%20and%20safety%20codes%2C%20and%20their%20internal%20filters%20are%20capable%20of%20flagging%20others%2C%20said%20Rachel%20S.%20Doughty%2C%20a%20plaintiff%20attorney%20for%20the%20original%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20dangerous%20skin%20products%20have%20easily%20targeted%20%26quot%3Bred%20flags%26quot%3B%20in%20their%20listings%2C%20the%20plaintiffs%20had%20argued.%20Most%20were%20made%20in%20Mexico%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20for%20example.%20Products%20claiming%20to%20both%20whiten%20skin%20and%20treat%20acne%20were%20also%20red%20flags%2C%20because%20mercury%20is%20the%20only%20ingredient%20known%20to%20do%20both%2C%20they%20had%20argued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20an%20improvement%20in%20their%20website%20in%20the%20ten%20years%20since%20we%20filed%20the%20first%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Doughty%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20means%20you%20will%20have%20a%20harder%20time%20finding%20well-known%20skin-whitening%20and%20lightening%20products%20on%20their%20website%20that%20have%20mercury%20in%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20hopes%20that%20the%20settlement%20will%20prompt%20Amazon%20to%20be%20vigilant%20in%20policing%20its%20site%20for%20other%20potentially%20toxic%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hope%20that%20internally%2C%20they%20don't%20want%20this%20to%20happen%20again%2C%20and%20that%20they%20are%20looking%20for%20other%20things%20that%20may%20have%20mercury%2C%20lead%2C%20cadmium%2C%20and%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20other%20chemicals%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement%20that%20the%20company%20does%20not%20tolerate%20illegal%20or%20evasive%20behavior%20from%20the%20businesses%20that%20sell%20through%20its%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20case%2C%20all%20products%20in%20question%20were%20evasively%20listed%20by%20bad%20actors%20and%20once%20identified%2C%20were%20removed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20proactive%20measures%20in%20place%20to%20prevent%20prohibited%20products%20from%20being%20listed%20and%20we%20continuously%20monitor%20our%20store.%20If%20we%20discover%20a%20product%20was%20undetected%20by%20our%20automated%20checks%2C%20we%20address%20the%20issue%20immediately%20and%20refine%20our%20controls.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-agrees-6-million-settlement-skin-cream-mercury-lawsuit-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A17383