ents%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20like%20alpha%20hydroxy%20acids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC8389214%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2021%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20niacinamide%20has%20anti-inflammatory%20effects%2C%20helps%20to%20prevent%20skin%20cell%20damage%2C%20and%20increases%20collagen%20production.%20It%20can%20also%20stop%20melanin%20from%20reaching%20the%20surface%20layers%20of%20the%20skin%2C%20which%20is%20what%20causes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fhyperpigmentation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehyperpigmentation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20found%20that%20the%20potential%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC8389214%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebenefits%20of%20niacinamide%3C%2Fa%3E%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELess%20visible%20pores%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20even%20skin%20tone%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReduced%20redness%2Fblotchiness%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIncreased%20hydration%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDiminished%20dark%20spots%2C%20wrinkles%2C%20and%20fine%20lines%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b23c14fe-2d7a-47b9-8bbf-8345ef5aed30%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EVitamin%20C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20this%20dermatologist-approved%20ingredient%20gets%20so%20much%20hype%20is%20that%20it's%20backed%20by%20science.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC5579659%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2017%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20vitamin%20C%20has%20several%20skin-supporting%20superpowers%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20it%20stimulates%20collagen%20production%20and%20provides%20antioxidant%20protection%20against%20UV%20skin%20damage.%20Studies%20examined%20in%20this%20review%20found%20that%20regularly%20applying%20vitamin%20C%20to%20the%20skin%20topically%20can%20improve%20skin%20dryness%2C%20roughness%2C%20tightness%2C%20and%20tone%20while%20reducing%20wrinkle%20depth.%20It%20also%20hinders%20the%20production%20of%20melanin%2C%20which%20is%20the%20substance%20that%20gives%20your%20skin%20pigment%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20vitamin%20C%20can%20help%20to%20reduce%20and%20prevent%20sun%20spots%20and%20other%20kinds%20of%20discoloration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKapoor%20recommends%20a%20product%20with%20vitamin%20C%20for%20anyone%20who's%20looking%20to%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAddress%20uneven%20skin%20tone%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReduce%20the%20appearance%20of%20dark%20spots%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBrighten%20their%20skin%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20in%20mind%20that%20vitamin%20C%20can%20actually%20increase%20your%20skin's%20sensitivity%20to%20the%20sun%2C%20says%20Spearman.%20That's%20why%20she%20recommends%20slathering%20on%20sunscreen%20daily%20while%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fvitamin-c-for-skin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evitamin%20C%20for%20skin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20particularly%20if%20you're%20applying%20it%20in%20the%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVitamin%20C%20is%20a%20generally%20well-tolerated%20skincare%20ingredient%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20important%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20potency.%20Studies%20have%20found%20that%20you%20may%20be%20more%20prone%20to%20irritation%20if%20you%20use%20a%20product%20with%20vitamin%20C%20in%20concentrations%20above%2020%25.%20According%20to%20Kapoor%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fbest-vitamin-c-serum%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20vitamin%20C%20serums%3C%2Fa%3E%20feature%20a%20potency%20between%2010%25%20and%2020%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222dcdd7d9-e224-46e3-822b-6e35e8cdfbe0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeptides%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20non-irritating%20retinol%20alternatives%20go%2C%20you%20truly%20can't%20beat%20peptides.%20In%20fact%2C%20peptides%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.academicallderm.com%2Fblog%2Fpeptides-in-skincare-the-science-behind-the-results%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20soothing%20anti-inflammatory%20properties%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20making%20them%20an%20ideal%20fit%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fskincare-products-for-sensitive-skin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esensitive%20skin%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeptides%20are%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.clevelandclinic.org%2Fpeptides-for-skin%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20blocks%20for%20two%20skin-enhancing%20proteins%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20collagen%20and%20elastin%20%E2%80%94%20and%20because%20of%20this%2C%20they%20can%20help%20your%20skin%20maintain%20its%20structure%20and%20flexibility%2C%20thus%20warding%20off%20signs%20of%20aging%20like%20sagging%2C%20wrinkles%2C%20and%20crepey%20skin.%20According%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS1756464621003297%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2021%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20peptides%20can%20also%20reduce%20sun%20spots%20by%20encouraging%20skin%20cells%20to%20regenerate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Kapoor%2C%20peptides%20are%20not%20only%20gentle%20on%20the%20skin%20but%20can%20help%20repair%20damaged%20skin.%20While%20peptides%20can%20benefit%20anyone%20looking%20to%20improve%20their%20complexion%2C%20he%20says%20they're%20especially%20well-suited%20to%20anyone%20who%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERecently%20had%20a%20skin%20procedure%2C%20like%20a%20laser%20treatment%2C%20and%20is%20looking%20to%20speed%20up%20the%20repair%20process%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIs%20interested%20in%20slowing%20signs%20of%20aging%20or%20recently%20began%20recognizing%20wrinkles%20and%20fine%20lines%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIs%20seeking%20firmer%2C%20more%20taut%20skin%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC6981886%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmall%202019%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20women%20over%20the%20age%20of%2040%20found%20that%20using%20peptides%20can%20result%20in%20a%20noticeable%20improvement%20in%20the%20appearance%20of%20wrinkles%2C%20including%20crow's%20feet%20near%20the%20eyes%2C%20frown%20lines%2C%20horizontal%20forehead%20lines%2C%20nasolabial%20folds%2C%20and%20horizontal%20neck%20lines.%20Another%20small%202016%20study%20found%20that%20after%20using%20a%20peptide%20serum%20for%2014%20weeks%2C%20participants%20noticed%20a%20significant%20improvement%20in%20skin%20softness%2C%20firmness%2C%20smoothness%2C%20luminosity%2C%20and%20radiance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20beauty%20of%20peptides%20is%20that%20because%20they're%20so%20gentle%2C%20you%20can%20use%20them%20daily%20without%20risking%20irritation%2C%20says%20Spearman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c4d991b4-43cf-451e-bfb2-9e0f1481470a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERosehip%20Oil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERosehip%20oil%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20for%20the%20record%2C%20is%20not%20the%20same%20thing%20as%20rose%20oil%20%E2%80%94%20is%20made%20by%20pressing%20the%20fruit%20of%20the%20rose%20plant%2C%20which%20can%20be%20found%20underneath%20the%20flower%20petals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Spearman%2C%20rosehip%20oil%20is%20rich%20in%20skin-nourishing%20vitamins%20A%2C%20C%2C%20and%20E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4655903%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eessential%20fatty%20acids%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Vitamin%20A%20is%20essential%20for%20producing%20collagen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20these%20nutrients%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.clevelandclinic.org%2Frosehip-oil-benefits-for-skin-and-hair%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erosehip%20oil%20may%20help%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EImprove%20skin%20moisture%20levels%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReduce%20and%20ward%20off